==English==

==Etymology==
From German ''[[Sturmtruppen]]'', from ''[[sturm]]'' (storm) + ''[[truppen]]'' (troops). 

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A German soldier trained in special infiltration tactics, introduced around the end of World War I.
# An Imperial stormtrooper, a fictional soldier from the ''Star Wars'' series of films.

